tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,Wait time,
context: Prenatal Checkup,Pregnancy Scan,Pre and Post Delivery Care,Pregnancy Check Up,
review:
My experience with Dr Madhushree is incomparable with absolutely any other doctor so far. She is the most approachable, humble, genuine *** ************* doctor I’ve dealt with. She was extremely patient to answer every single query I had and also provided extensive emotional support during my pregnancy. 
Her skills are undoubtedly perfect, there was not even one instance where she faultered. 
She was completely transparent about everything and yet at the same time completely put us at ease with her personality and attitude. Although my baby was IUGR and premature by a month, she had taken all the necessary precautions to ensure that my baby didn’t have to be admitted to the NICU for even a single day. 
In this day and age it’s extremely rare to find doctors who push for a normal delivery. Even though I had to undergo csection due to medical conditions, her first preference was to try for a normal delivery. 
One of the best memories of this pregnancy is my experience with Dr Madhushree.

tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,Wait time,
review:
My wife Varalaxmi delivered a healthy baby boy on 01st March 2018. My wife and our newborn baby both are doing well.

Though, we are around 600 Kms away from our native, parents and our relatives, we still preferred to undergo the delivery procedure of our baby at Motherhood Hospital, Sahakar Nagar, only because we felt that we are in the safest hands. My wife was in consultation (For pregnancy care & delivery) with Dr. Madhushree VijayaKumar, *** ** *** ****** *** *** **** ******* ** **** **** *****
Since, our case was slightly critical, the doctor treated this as a special case and provided utmost care and support to my wife throughout. On an appointment, she would always takes time to answers all our questions and never seems to be in a rush to move on to the next patient. There are no unanswered questions, doubts, or confusion at the end of our appointment. 

She is the nicest, most caring doctor we have ever met – she even takes time to answer our calls during an emergency/distress situation to advice my wife and was always approchable and available on the phone round the clock. 

Thank you so much, Doctor(Madam) for being so professional, friendly, caring and patient with us throughout. We all three of us (including our baby) will be always thankfull to you for the exceptional care and support. 

Thank you,
Vijay Kumar TP/Varalaxmi

tags: None
review: **** ****** **** ****** ***** ** ******** **** * ********* ****** *** *** I had a normal delivery under her guidance which is a rarity these days. Especially in a big city and at a commercial hospital. I was willing to go for c-sec so as to avoid the pain but she insisted on a normal delivery and helped me make the decision and smoothly go through with it. She is a blessing for any pregnant woman. The warmth and support she provides makes one really indebted to her. I went for delivery in motherhood sahakar nagar without an insurance only coz i did trust her to do the best for me and my child. I had researched a lot online before finalizing a doctor when i moved to bangalore 5 months pregnant but i did not find much data. It was only by chance that i went to see dr madhushree on the recommendation of a local parlour lady. I had a very happy experience that i wish to share with everyone looking for a reliable doctor.

tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,
review:
Excellent doctor. Proactive, efficient and friendly. 
Feel blessed that we consulted her through my second n third trimester. Had a normal delivery with forceps intervention this July. N its such a relief as I have bounced back to life soon after. It's important to have a doctor whom you can trust and speak to without hesitation and it's wonderful that she helped me sail through all my complications with immense confidence. Also, with so many women undergoing C sections (4 cases I have heard in my own circle in the last 60 days) for various reasons, it's all the more important to have faith that your doctor will try her best to ensure a safe and a normal delivery.

tags: Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Wait time,
review:
My first impression when i went to the doctor was that she was one of the most comfortable doctor ive met 
Friendliness is not the ultimate thing we need as patients i realised
I went ther with  severe UTI symptoms
I was put on antibiotics for five days after which she asked me to sms my culture reports on her whatsapp number and shwe would change it accordingly !

Well after five days after experiencing ****** **** ******* **** low bp dizziness vomitting leg cramps etc i messaged her to please change the medicines ***** ***** ** ** *** ******* ** 
All she replied was continue same meds

Repeatedly requesting her to tell me which medicines to continue since shes given 5 of them for different no of days *** **** *********** *** **** ******* i asked her to change it

No Response ! For four days no response ! And i can see her online checking my messages 

Fourth day i lost my cool and sent her a stinker explaining wht she is doin is not acceptable

Typical case of “over commitment and underdelivery” ! 

I was told again continue same meds ******* ** ********** ******* *** ** **** ******* and then i was told to change my consultant if i want 

And all this was because she was on a “vacation” with her family. 
It doesnt take more ten seconds to tell me what to do and how to proceed !

tags: Doctor friendliness,Treatment satisfaction,
review:
To all those who are searching online/PRACTO for a good Gynecologist , she is the one for sure. She is ******* *expert and has very good understanding of  every bit related to pregnancy and all other stuff . She always has time and is reachable to  her patients round the clock . She guides them , right from diet , excercises and medications that required for a healthy pregnancy process . Under her able guidance and supervision, one will end-up having a normal delivery without a choice. *** ** *** **** ** ***** ** ********* *** *** ** ** *** ******* *** **** * 
Thank you madam for your warmth, care ,support , guidance and yes ofcourse medication . We will always be indebted and grateful to your help ! 

Give a try once  for a healthy and safe pregnancy !

tags: None
review:
* ***** *** *** ** *** ** *** **** *** ******** ************* ** *******. She talks to her patients in detail and give them ample time to clarify all their doubts eventough it can be silly too. She tries for normal delivery and recommend the right excersice and diet which is very helpful. She is always available on call and message which cheer up any worrisome mom to be.
I am happy that I have choosen her as my gynaecologist. 
Eventhough  I had some complications in pregnancy, she helped me cross it smoothly. Would definitely recommend her.
